  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from an app lock can be challenging, especially if the app has its own deletion mechanism. Here are steps you can take to try to recover your deleted photos:\n\n1. **Check the App's Recovery Options**: \n   - Some app lock applications have a built-in recovery feature where deleted items may be stored temporarily. Look for any recovery or trash folder within the app.\n\n2. **Check Your Device\u2019s Gallery App**:\n   - Sometimes, photos might be moved rather than permanently deleted. Check the \"Recently Deleted\" folder in your device\u2019s gallery app if it has one. Photos in this folder may be recoverable for a limited time.\n\n3. **Use a File Recovery App**:\n   - There are various third-party file recovery apps available on app stores that can scan your device for deleted files. Some popular options include DiskDigger, EaseUS MobiSaver, or Recuva. Install one and follow the instructions to scan your device.\n\n4. **Check Cloud Backups**:\n   - If you have cloud storage services (like Google Photos, iCloud, OneDrive, etc.) set up for automatic backups, check if your photos are backed up there. You can recover them directly from your cloud storage account.\n\n5. **Connect to a Computer**:\n   - Connect your device to a computer and use file recovery software to scan your device's storage. This can sometimes be more effective, especially if you can create a disk image of your device.\n\n6. **Contact Support**:\n   - If you\u2019re using a specific app lock application, you might want to contact their customer support for assistance. They might have specific mechanisms in place for data recovery.\n\n7. **Backup Your Data Regularly**:\n   - In the future, consider regularly backing up your photos to prevent loss from app deletions. Use both cloud services and physical backups.\n\nPlease remember that the success of recovery largely depends on how the data was deleted and whether the storage space has been overwritten since the deletion. It\u2019s always a good idea to act quickly to increase the chances of successful recovery.",
